               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donor and Metropolitan ʾabba Bärtolomewos; two initial lines of each section of the text; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals; some other words, e.g., ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 6v,9r, 11v), qǝdmä wängel (e.g., fols. 32v, 35r, 48v), wä-tǝbl (e.g., fols. 32r, 62r, 68v), ʾǝskä (e.g., fols. 47r, 51r).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text II, Śǝrʿatä mǝnkwäsǝnna “The Order of the Monastic Profession”, has similar readings with Grebaut’s edition of ሥርዓተ፡ ምንኵስና፡ ቅድስት (S. GREBAUT, Rituel éthiopien de prise d’habit, Paris 1940) but the order appears completely different. Fol. 85r (ጸሎት፡ እምድኅረ፡ አቅነትከ) matches with p. 10 of the edition (ጸሎት፡ ሶበ፡ ያቀንቱ፡ መነኮሳት); fol. 85r matches p. 14 of the edition (ጸሎት፡ ላዕለ፡ ደናግል) .</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
